TITLE: Implementing onBeforePrerenderStart Hook for i18n Data Loading in Vike
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to use the onBeforePrerenderStart() hook to load localized data and generate URLs for each locale during pre-rendering. It demonstrates an alternative approach to onPrerenderStart() when data depends on localization.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vikejs/vike/blob/main/docs/pages/i18n/+Page.mdx#2025-04-17_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// pages/product/+onBeforePrerenderStart.js

// This example doesn't use onPrerenderStart() but, instead,
// uses onBeforePrerenderStart() to duplicate and localize URLs and their pageContext
export { onBeforePrerenderStart }

async function onBeforePrerenderStart() {
  // Load data
  const products = await Product.findAll()

  // Set pageContext + localize
  const urlsWithPageContext = []
  products.forEach(product => {
    ['en-US', 'de-DE', 'fr-FR'].forEach(locale => {
      urlsWithPageContext.push({
        url: `/${locale}/product/${product.id}`,
        pageContext: {
          locale,
          product,
          data: {
            product: {
              name: product.name,
              description: product.description,
              price: product.price,
              // ...
            }
          }
        }
      })
    })
  })

  return urlsWithPageContext
}
```

