TITLE: Implementing Fetch Polyfill for Auth.js Server-Side Authentication
DESCRIPTION: Server-side implementation for adding fetch polyfill support to enable Auth.js getSession() functionality. Uses node-fetch to patch the global object with fetch implementation for Node.js environments before version 18.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vikejs/vike/blob/main/docs/pages/AuthJS/+Page.mdx#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// server.js

// Only install the polyfill on the server (e.g. Express.js). Browsers already implement
// `fetch()` natively and it would be wasteful to load the polyfill on the browser-side.

// Use node-fetch@2 instead of node-fetch@3 if your `package.json#type` isn't `"module"`.
// Or some other `fetch()` polyfill, e.g. `cross-fetch`.
import fetch, { Headers, Request, Response } from 'node-fetch'

if (!globalThis.fetch) {
  globalThis.fetch = fetch
  globalThis.Headers = Headers
  globalThis.Request = Request
  globalThis.Response = Response
}
```

