TITLE: Customizing Asset Injection with injectFilter
DESCRIPTION: Example of using injectFilter to customize how and where asset tags are injected into the HTML. Shows how to implement custom preloading logic for specific asset types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vikejs/vike/blob/main/docs/pages/preloading/+Page.mdx#2025-04-17_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// /renderer/+onRenderHtml.js

export { onRenderHtml }

async function onRenderHtml(pageContext) {
  // ...

  const documentHtml = escapeInject`<!DOCTYPE html>
    <html>
      <body>
        <div id="root">${stream}</div>
      </body>
    </html>`

  const injectFilter = (assets) => {
    assets.forEach(asset => {
      // Preload images
      if (asset.assetType === 'image') {
        asset.inject = 'HTML_BEGIN'
      }
    })
  }

  return { documentHtml, injectFilter }
}
```

